timeline.message:
Provide a way to build `RetryStrategy`

Motivation:

Currently `RetryStrategy` supports factory methods.
If a user wants to make a complex `RetryStrategy`, he/she should implement their own `RetryStrategy`
By offering `RetryStrategyBuilder`, users can easily build `RetryStrategy`.

For example:

```java
Backoff backoffOn503 = ...;
Backoff backoffOn500 = ...;

// Before:
RetryStrategy retryStrategy = RetryStrategy.onStatus((status, unused) -> {
    if (status == HttpStatus.SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE) {
        return backoffOn503;
    }
    if (status == HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR) {
        return backoffOn500;
    }
    return null;
});

// After:
RetryStrategy retryStrategy =
        RetryStrategy.builder()
                     .onStatus(HttpStatus.SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE, backoffOn503)
                     .onStatus(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, backoffOn500)
                     .build();
```

Or build a more complex strategy
```java
RetryStrategy strategy =
        RetryStrategy.builder()
                     .onUnProcessed(unProcessBackOff)
                     .onException()
                     .onServerErrorStatus(statusErrorBackOff)
                     .onStatus(HttpStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS, statusBackOff)
                     .addRetryStrategy((ctx, cause) -> {
                         if (ctx.log().isAvailable(RequestLogProperty.RESPONSE_HEADERS)) {
                             final HttpStatus responseStatus =
                                     ctx.log().partial().responseHeaders().status();
                             if (responseStatus.isClientError()) {
                                 return CompletableFuture.completedFuture(clientErrorBackOff);
                             }
                         }
                         return CompletableFuture.completedFuture(null);
                     })
                     .build();
```

Modifications:

- Add `RetryStrategyBuilder` for building `RetrySratategy`.
- Add `RetryStrategyBindingBuilder` for building `RetryStrategy` fluently.
- Breaking
  - `RetryStrategy.onServerErrorStatus()` does not retry anymore when an exception is raised.
     Use `RetryStrategyBuilder.onServerErrorStatus()` with `RetryStrategyBuilder.onException(...)`
- Deprecation
  - `RetryStrategy.onStatus(backoffFunction)` has been deprecated in favor of
    `RetryStrategyBuilder.onStatus(...)` and `RetryStrategyBuilder.onException(...)`.
  - `RetryStrategy.onException(backoffFunction)` has been deprecated in favor of
    `RetryStrategyBuilder.onException(...)`.

Result:

- Fixes #1634
- You can now easily build `RetryStrategy` using its builder.

