I don't think AND operation in builder makes sense for a response status or an exception.
How about changing onIdempotentMethods() to ifIdempotentMethods()?
RetryRule.builder()
         .ifIdempotentMethods()
         .onServerErrorStatus()
         .onUnprocessed()
         .thenBackoff()
         .or(RetryRule.onStatus(HttpStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS));
or just give up changing on* methods and
We can change the return type builder methods to select only one on* methods.
class RetryRuleBuilder {
    public RetryRuleBuilder onIdempotentMethods() {
